OL,3,CIran strike risks: Have we forgotten
OL,4,Cthe cautionary tale of Iraq?
OL,6,FIran is separated from Iraq by a
OL,7,Fborder and a letter. It also stands
OL,8,Faccused of wanting to possess and
OL,9,Fwield weapons of mass destruction;
OL,10,Fit's also ruled over by an odious
OL,11,Fregime; it also faces heavy sanctions
OL,12,Fand it has also been weakened by a
OL,13,Fprevious conflict.
OL,15,FToday 23 years ago, I was part of the
OL,16,FITV News team waiting in Baghdad for
OL,17,Fthe war to begin. Naively, I thought
OL,18,Fthat nothing could be worse than the
OL,19,Frule of Saddam Hussein.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
